item.title: Calah add a quote by Dr. David Hawkins
item.description: "We change the world not by what we say or do, but as a consequence of what we have become." -- Dr. David Hawkins

item.title: Calah add a quote by F. Scott Fitzgerald
item.description: "That is part of the beauty of all literature. You discover that your longings are universal longings, that you're not lonely and isolated from anyone. You belong." -- F. Scott Fitzgerald

item.title: Calah add a quote by Pablo Neruda
item.description: "I love you without knowing how, or when, or from where. I love you simply, without problems or pride: I love you in this way because I do not know any other way of loving but this, in which there is no I or you, so intimate that your hand upon my chest is my hand, so intimate that when I fall asleep your eyes close." -- Pablo Neruda

item.title: Calah add a quote by Friedrich Nietzsche
item.description: "...throw roses into the abyss and say: 'here is my thanks to the monster who didn't succeed in swallowing me alive." -- Friedrich Nietzsche
